      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NANGAR MCGRAW (5) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.3 lengths (22.95) behind CREEPING MYLO at this track. Awkwardly drawn but a fast beginner who can clear the ruck early. Overdue and expected to feature again. LET'S GO JUDE (3) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 5 lengths at this track in a handy 18.16 beating Gladstone Bag. Winner at her latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. PANDA UNLEASHED (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished second (25.43) at Gunnedah latest and might be close to finding winning form again. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Bold showing expected. MOTOR CITY CHIEF (2) is in the mix despite missing out at this track last time.",
